headlines.description: — Khris Middleton had 27 points, eight rebounds and seven assists in three quarters, as the Milwaukee Bucks breezed to a 130-105 victory over the Minnesota Timberwolves on Wednesday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Middleton leads Bucks in 130-105 breeze by Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Taurean Prince scored a season-high 25 points with six 3-pointers, Jarrett Allen had 15 points and eight rebounds in his first action since March 26 and the Cleveland Cavaliers handed the Charlotte Hornets their third straight loss at home Wednesday...
headlines.shortLinkText: Allen scores 15 in return, Cavaliers beat Hornets 103-90

headlines.description: - Joel Embiid had 39 points and 13 rebounds and the Philadelphia 76ers beat Brooklyn 123-117 on Wednesday night in an anticipated matchup that fizzled with the Nets missing their biggest stars.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid, 76ers top undermanned Nets 123-117 for 1st in East

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — OG Anunoby scored 22 points, Pascal Siakam had 20 points and 11 rebounds and the short-handed Toronto Raptors beat the San Antonio Spurs 117-112 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anunoby, Siakam rally Raptors past Spurs 117-112

headlines.description: — Reggie Jackson sank a jumper with 2.3 seconds left against his former team, giving the Los Angeles Clippers their seventh straight victory, 100-98 over the Detroit Pistons on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson's jumper gives Clippers 100-98 win over Pistons

headlines.description: — James Ennis scored 22 points, Wendell Carter Jr. added 19 points and 12 rebounds, and the Orlando Magic snapped a six-game losing streak by beating the Chicago Bulls 115-106 on Wednesday night despite big performances by Zach LaVine and Nikola Vucevic.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ennis, Carter Jr. come up big as Magic beat Bulls 115-106

events.name: New York Knicks at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Julius Randle scored 32 points against his former team and the New York Knicks clamped down defensively on Zion Williamson for a 116-106 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle nets 32 as Knicks limit Zion, beat Pelicans 116-106

headlines.description: — Caris LeVert scored 27 points, Domantas Sabonis added 22 and Malcolm Brogdon fell just short of a triple-double as the Indiana Pacers beat the Houston Rockets 132-124 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Indiana sends Houston to 4th straight loss, 132-124

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 25 of his 42 points in the third quarter, and the Golden State Warriors ran away from the Oklahoma City Thunder 147-109 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry's 42, Green's triple-double lead Warriors past Thunder

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic hit a leaning, lunging 3-pointer as time expired to give the Dallas Mavericks a 114-113 victory over the Memphis Grizzlies on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic's 3 at buzzer leads Mavericks past Grizzlies 114-113

video.headline: Doncic beats buzzer to win game for Mavs

highlights.headline: Doncic beats buzzer to win game for Mavs
highlights.description: Luka Doncic works his magic as he drains the one-footed 3-pointer to win the game for the Mavericks.

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 17 points, 11 assists and 10 rebounds for his 15th triple-double of the season to lead the Denver Nuggets over the Miami Heat 123-106 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic's triple-double leads Nuggets over Heat 123-106

headlines.description: — Russell Westbrook recorded his 170th career triple-double, Bradley Beal scored 31 points, and the Washington Wizards ended their longest road trip of the season by beating the Sacramento Kings 123-111 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Westbrook posts 24th triple-double of season in Wizards' win
